<strong>Project 1 – Home Monitoring & Response System for Older/Ill People</strong>
Our society is struggling to care for its aging population so that people can live at home for as long as possible, safely and with dignity. This project is to design and build prototype systems that facilitate this. Groups can define their own goals within this context. There are a few global 
  requirements:
• The prototype(s) must include example sensors (cheaper, less accurate sensors are okay as long as the functionality of the system can be demonstrated, and the documentation includes recommendations for improved sensors, and why they are necessary
• The occupants must not be able to harm themselves or others in the monitored space by setting parameters that will lead to accidents or will effectively disarm the system
• The prototype(s) must include the monitoring/response side of the system
• Care must be taken to make the systems robust in the face of hardware malfunction, malicious intrusion, environmental effects, and also with respect to future changes in the system
• The project can target long-term care facility use rather than, or as well as, in-home use
• The system must be easy for administrators to use and it must also be as non-intrusive for the clients as possible
• There may be levels of client interaction dependent on the target facility/clients
